ce:section.ce:para:
Herein, we report a yellow-emissive CD-based nanosensor for full-range intracellular pH imaging. The prepared yellow-emissive CDs (Y-CDs) were obtained through one-pot solvothermal treatment of o-phenylenediamine (o-PD). Compared with the features of other CDs synthesized using phenylenediamine as precursors (Table S2), the Y-CDs exhibit excellent fluorescence emission at 570 nm (λex = 450 nm) and display a large Stokes shift (120 nm) (Scheme 1
                     ) [23–25]. The pK
                     a value of this nanoprobe was found to be 6.4, and it displayed a good linear relationship with pH in a response range of 4.0–8.2 in buffer solution. The unique physicochemical features make this nanosensor effective as a fluorimetric pH indicator for imaging full-range intracellular pH values.
